cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the effectiveness of different approaches to data archiving in scientific research, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the management and dissemination of digital information, including research data. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) are also relevant as they deal with the storage and retrieval of information. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are less likely but still possible categories as they may address issues related to data privacy and ethical considerations in data sharing.
